data.title: W. S. Crichton Medal winners
data.text:
1. Gary Bell (footballer) ( age: 70 )

Gary Bell (born 4 April 1947 in Stourbridge) is an English former professional footballer. During his career, he made over 350 appearances in The Football League in spells with Cardiff City, Hereford United and Newport County.

2. Gary Moore ( age: 65 ) ( Musician, songwriter, record producer )

4. Goran Šubara ( age: 30 )

5. Ivo Trenchev ( age: 45 )

Ivo Trenchev (born 4 April 1972) is a Bulgarian footballer who plays for Septemvri Simitli as a defender.
